The paper presents a machine learning-powered iterative combinatorial auction, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The use of machine learning algorithms to improve preference elicitation also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the computational practicality of the auction, which relates to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the auction involves multiple agents interacting with each other, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
